reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Far and away the best
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely the best mechanical toothbrushes I use, nothing else compares. They're ergonomic and comfortable to hold, the bristles are soft and plentiful and curved in such a way that it's especially easy to brush the back teeth, and they're nice and heavy-duty to boot.They stay in good condition for longer than other (mechanical) toothbrushes, and when I switch to a new one after 3 months, I sanitize the previous one and use it around the house for deep-cleaning. Even after functioning as a very solid toothbrush for that amount of time, it's still perfect for cleaning - especially for getting into tight corners, grout lines, shower tiles etc. Then after 3 months I repeat the cycle - I start using a new one for my teeth, sanitize/recycle the previous one for cleaning tasks, and then I retire the oldest one (right into the trash can, that is). Perfect toothbrush, exceptional deep-cleaning tool, fantastic in every way. Cannot recommend these enough. I hate how much I like a specific toothbrush.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars In my 24 years of living...
reviews.reviewText: This is the best damn toothbrush I have ever used, and here's a lengthy review to explain why...normally, I'd go to target or walmart and grab a toothbrush that looks decent and go. normally, i would do the same thing, but 9/10 of the time, i would never buy the same variety.first off, let me give some context: i am BIG on texture. felt, jean, fur-type, clothes, food, and yes, even toothbrush.so for my texture people, this review is yours.i bought a pack of these a year ago, and (not to exaggerate, but—) it changed my life. had to go back to target and but it again, but on the third buy, they stopped selling them. it took me about 20 minutes to find these guys, and it's the exact same, despite the original packs' side bristles being orange instead of white.the bristles HUG your teeth. it feels like scratching an itch in your mouth that you never thought to scratch. it doesn't feel like i have to push the toothbrush down to REALLY get in there.and you really don't need to! most toothbrush i use, whenever i spit out the toothpaste, rarely ever show food bits from in between teeth. i have to use a floss and there's always a piece of food or two w each tooth (after 2.5min of brushing). with this toothbrush, however, i could actually see the food bits. flossing took care of the plaque, and only one tooth had a food bit.my last toothbrush of this kind lasted me a month and a half. i don't really know if that's too long or too little between each toothbrush, but i also just like to keep things until they look unusable... so here we are!listen, this may not be the toothbrush for you, but it is for me. yall should go ahead and give it a shot!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I've tried a LOT of toothbrushes, and this one's my favorite. It has a good grip, looks great, and you can feel it working when you're brushing. The real test is popcorn. This can reach it and get it out. It is extremely effective. A trusted brand as well. I used to think it was "Ordall-B" because of the Brit doing the commercials. They also last long because they're so well-built. It isn't the softest, but soft enough. That's not a problem so far as I'm concerned. This is the one I'm sticking with.

I bought this product thinking it was the Oral B Pro Health toothbrush. It looks much the same but when I compared it to the Pro Health toothbrushes that I had bought in store I realized that the head on this one is smaller. Brush may work ok, but be aware that it is not as advertised. Also, there is a label on the back of the package that indicates these toothbrushes were purchased for a dental office, so resold stock? I feel like I was deceived and will not order this again.
